File: lichen/subsys/lichen/meshtastic/adapter.c:1067-1075

  static void sanitize_peer_snapshot(struct lichen_meshtastic_peer_snapshot *peer)
  {
      if (peer->has_long_name) {
          peer->long_name[sizeof(peer->long_name) - 1U] = '\0';
          if (peer->long_name[0] == '\0') {
              peer->has_long_name = false;
          }
      }
  }

This forces NUL-termination at the last byte, which is correct. But it assumes long_name has at least 1 byte capacity.

Looking at the struct definition in adapter.h:214:
  char long_name[LICHEN_MESHTASTIC_NODE_NAME_MAX];

And in codec.h:46:
  #define LICHEN_MESHTASTIC_NODE_NAME_MAX 32U

So there's space. But if NODE_NAME_MAX were ever configured to 0, this would be out of bounds.

Add: BUILD_ASSERT(LICHEN_MESHTASTIC_NODE_NAME_MAX >= 1, 'name buffer must have space for terminator');
